The paper deals with wiretap channels, which are a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on the state-dependent wiretap channel, which is a specific type of wiretap channel that involves random states (cs.CR). The paper also discusses coding schemes and achieving secrecy-capacity, which are topics in coding theory (cs.CC). The use of superposition coding and the soft-covering lemma suggest that the paper may also be relevant to signal processing and communications (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
